{"parentUuid":"837194c9-d72f-4e43-95bb-0eca1cb53740","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"53f5148a-6791-4be6-a2fc-f4eaf65be586","agentId":"a9be7dfc4c563b791","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DSGUhfmB41ba8fAyHbPAYu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tfeature: usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\n3\tcriteria_total: 21\n4\tdelegated_criteria: [AC18]\n5\tderived_from: PROJECT.md + .pipeline/requirements.md (resolved items) + STRIDE + input-surface + DAST-readiness\n6\tnotes: >\n7\t  Feature-level definition-of-done. Implementation builds to these; testing maps each ID to a\n8\t  test (criteria_covered). AC18 is delegated to the security stage (ASVS reconciliation), so\n9\t  testing marks it covered:false, delegated:\"security\". No performance k6 load AC: the export is\n10\t  a reporting route with a documented p95 sanity check (AC16); the binding perf constraint is the\n11\t  negative one (AC15 — existing endpoints/budgets untouched).\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\t| ID | Criterion | File / layer | How verified |\n15\t|---|---|---|---|\n16\t| AC1 | Response is RFC 4180 CSV via stdlib `csv`: header row exactly `customer_id,metric,window_start,total_quantity` (brief column order), CRLF line endings, fields containing comma/quote/newline quoted | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit (dialect, header, CRLF, quoting) + integration end-to-end body assertion |\n17\t| AC2 | Optional `customer_id`/`metric`/`from`/`to` filters applied (reusing existing allowlist types + window bounds); all omitted → full supported range | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Unit (schema) + integration (each filter narrows the row set; none → all caller rows) |\n18\t| AC3 | `from`/`to` validation: timezone-aware, `from <= to`, both within `[now-90d, now+1h]`, naive datetime rejected | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py` | Unit (accept/reject cases incl. naive, inverted range, out-of-window) |\n19\t| AC4 | Input validation (non-waivable): malformed / wrong-type / unknown / out-of-range query param → 422 `validation_failed`; `extra=\"forbid\"` rejects unknown params | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | Unit + integration (422 envelope with `code=validation_failed`) |\n20\t| AC5 | Rate limit: post-auth **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** throttle applies (principal-keyed); two principals on one client IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (reuses `src/auth/rate_limit.py`) | Integration two-principals-one-IP discriminating test |\n21\t| AC6 | Authorization: any authenticated key (ingest or admin) may export; unauthenticated/invalid → 401; no scope gate | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/auth` | Integration (ingest key 200, admin key 200, no/invalid key 401) |\n22\t| AC7 | Tenant isolation: export returns ONLY the caller's `api_key_id` rows; two tenants' data never cross (explicit `api_key_id` filter is the primary control; RLS is backstop) | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration two-tenant test (tenant A's export excludes tenant B's rows) |\n23\t| AC8 | Row cap: a result exceeding 100,000 rows → 422 `validation_failed` (\"narrow filters\"), **no partial body streamed** (pre-flight count before any response byte) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (>100k rows → 422, response body is the envelope not CSV) |\n24\t| AC9 | Streaming constant memory: rows streamed as read via a server-side cursor, response not fully buffered before send | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration streaming-not-buffered sanity (first bytes observable before generator exhausted / bounded memory on a large export) |\n25\t| AC10 | CSV formula-injection escape: text cells (`customer_id`,`metric`) starting with `= + - @ \\t \\r` prefixed with `'`; control chars neutralized; numeric/timestamp cells untouched | `src/api/csv_export.py` | Unit (incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, each trigger, control chars, numeric/timestamp unaffected) + integration end-to-end |\n26\t| AC11 | Response headers: `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8`; `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv` (no tenant identifier in filename); inherits `nosniff` + `Cache-Control: no-store` | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/middleware.py` | Integration header assertions (incl. filename pattern, no tenant id) |\n27\t| AC12 | Empty result → 200 header-only CSV (single header row, zero data rows), never 404 | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration (caller with no matching rollups → 200, one CSV line) |\n28\t| AC13 | Deterministic ordering `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC`; identical exports are byte-stable | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (asserts row order over a seeded multi-row set) |\n29\t| AC14 | Value formats: `window_start` as UTC ISO-8601 with offset (identical to JSON response form); `total_quantity` as `str(Decimal)` (plain decimal, no scientific notation) | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit + integration (format assertions) |\n30\t| AC15 | No behavior change: `POST /v1/events`, `GET /v1/usage`, `PUT /v1/quotas` behavior/budgets/tests unchanged; no new Alembic revision / migration added | repo-wide (negative) | Existing test suites pass unchanged; no new file under `alembic/versions/` |\n31\t| AC16 | Performance budget: export route **p95 < 500 ms at the 100,000-row cap** (documented target, integration timing sanity — NOT a k6 load AC) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration timing sanity test at ~100k rows |\n32\t| AC17 | Audit logging: exactly one `usage.export` `info` event at completion (`userId`=opaque `api_key_id`, `operation`, `rowCount`, `capped`, `completed`, filter-presence booleans — no raw `customer_id`); over-cap request logged at `warn` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/logging` | Unit/integration (log fields present, no PII, one event; `warn` on over-cap) |\n33\t| AC18 | ASVS 5.0 L1/L2 controls for the triggered chapters (V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V13/V14/V16) present across the change set; recorded waivers honored | cross-cutting | Delegated to security stage (`delegated:\"security\"`) — reconciled against plan §ASVS Compliance |\n34\t| AC19 (DAST-1) | Served OpenAPI schema includes `GET /v1/usage/export` with its `200 text/csv` and `422` responses, matching the implemented route (not hand-drifted) | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Integration (assert route + responses present in `/openapi.json`) |\n35\t| AC20 (DAST-2) | A seeded non-production DAST test key (reuse the existing seeded key; credentials from env/secrets, never hardcoded) can call the export | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` (existing), test fixtures | Integration (seeded key successfully hits the export in staging/local) |\n36\t| AC21 (DAST-3) | Auth-context recorded for scanners: `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` header shape, documented in the plan and exercised by the integration auth path | plan §Auth, `src/auth/api_key.py` (existing) | Documented in plan + integration test uses this exact Bearer shape |\n37\t"}]},"uuid":"d9156eb2-fa04-4544-b31b-b479beba9dc8","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:43:04.202Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"837194c9-d72f-4e43-95bb-0eca1cb53740","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"d9156eb2-fa04-4544-b31b-b479beba9dc8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9be7dfc4c563b791","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcrtzmdY16byA8d2Z8zJC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BtNf1cwxX6TE81URychCwc","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\requirements.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":62,"cache_creation_input_tokens":23029,"cache_read_input_tokens":19408,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":23029,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcrtzkHRHwzvo28jLaSFk","attributionAgent":"plan-audit","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"faa4a329-d91b-472f-814a-74712012f5e3","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:43:04.557Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"faa4a329-d91b-472f-814a-74712012f5e3","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"53f5148a-6791-4be6-a2fc-f4eaf65be586","agentId":"a9be7dfc4c563b791","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BtNf1cwxX6TE81URychCwc","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Requirements — usage CSV export\n2\t\n3\tElicited 2026-07-09 (operator interview, pre-planning). Brief: PROJECT.md (GET /v1/usage/export,\n4\tcaller's rollups as CSV, existing API-key auth, no behavior change to existing endpoints,\n5\tno design source).\n6\t\n7\t## Resolved\n8\t\n9\t- What rows does the export return? → Every `usage_rollup` row under the authenticated\n10\t  `api_key_id`, with **optional** `customer_id` and `metric` query filters (reusing the\n11\t  existing validated types). No required params.\n12\t- Time-range semantics? → Optional `from`/`to` aware-datetime params, validated like the\n13\t  existing window bound (`from <= to`, both within `[now−90d, now+1h]`); omitted → the full\n14\t  supported range. Naive datetimes rejected (existing idiom).\n15\t- Size control? → **Streaming** response (constant memory, rows written as read) with a\n16\t  **hard cap of 100,000 rows**; a result exceeding the cap fails 422 `validation_failed`\n17\t  telling the caller to narrow filters. No pagination this slice.\n18\t- Who may export? → **Any authenticated key** (ingest or admin) — it is the caller's own\n19\t  tenant data, same read authority as GET /v1/usage; normal edge stack\n20\t  (require_api_key → Tier-2 per-key throttle).\n21\t- CSV formula injection? → **Escape formula-leading text cells** at the CSV-encoding\n22\t  boundary (OWASP defense: prefix `'` when a text cell starts with `=`, `+`, `-`, `@`,\n23\t  incl. tab/CR variants; control chars stripped/quoted). Numeric/timestamp columns untouched.\n24\t- Response headers? → `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8` +\n25\t  `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv`\n26\t  (no tenant identifiers in the filename).\n27\t- Dialect? → RFC 4180 via the stdlib csv module (no hand-rolled encoder): header row always\n28\t  present, exactly `customer_id,metric,window_start,total_quantity` (brief's column order);\n29\t  CRLF line endings; quote fields containing comma/quote/newline.\n30\t- Empty result? → **200 with a header-only CSV** (one shape for consumers; mirrors the\n31\t  existing zeros-not-404 contract).\n32\t- Ordering? → Deterministic `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC` (index-friendly;\n33\t  identical exports diff cleanly).\n34\t- Value formats? → `window_start` as the UTC ISO-8601 string with offset (identical to the\n35\t  JSON response's string form); `total_quantity` as a plain decimal string via `str(Decimal)`\n36\t  (no scientific notation).\n37\t- Perf posture? → Reporting route: **documented p95 target, NOT a k6 load AC** (proposed\n38\t  default: p95 < 500 ms at the 100k-row cap, verified by an integration timing sanity check).\n39\t  The binding perf criterion is negative: POST /v1/events' existing budget, tests, and code\n40\t  path are untouched (the brief's own no-behavior-change constraint).\n41\t- New stored data? → None — read-only feature over existing rollups; no migration, no new\n42\t  data-classification surface.\n43\t\n44\t## Open\n45\t\n46\t- The exact documented p95 target number for the export route (500 ms at the cap was the\n47\t  proposed default; low stakes — planning states a default or raises it at the checkpoint).\n48\t\n49\t## Out of scope\n50\t\n51\t- Pagination (`limit`/`offset`) — the row cap + filters are the size control this slice.\n52\t- Admin-only gating of exports — any authenticated key may export its own tenant's data.\n53\t- Other formats (JSON export, XLSX), compression (gzip), and scheduled/async export jobs.\n54\t- Any change to GET /v1/usage, POST /v1/events, PUT /v1/quotas, or their budgets/tests.\n55\t- Per-export audit logging beyond the standard structured request log.\n56\t"}]},"uuid":"05b91244-ffec-426f-9e9a-63930645a383","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:43:04.571Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"faa4a329-d91b-472f-814a-74712012f5e3","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
